ne5-27.0.jpg 720w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4e6jR42clMuHgNs0awiwKS_Vu0k=/0x0:1020x676/820x547/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 820w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kx5LLqRsD-EgqrqfQFKvm68BxFk=/0x0:1020x676/920x613/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 920w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IGSUPTv-vNssPLXDALE0y3OuKdY=/0x0:1020x676/1020x680/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1020w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Nr4iDhT01hCwtoaZu-rqlN7x8sQ=/0x0:1020x676/1120x747/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1120w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/96Zs73okNxrH_IA0naLo2_pMsyU=/0x0:1020x676/1220x813/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1220w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FCvb3kqpS71ri69N_ryOLhV8oaw=/0x0:1020x676/1320x880/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1320w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vs3UZmA4E43iHxqmarfN07xcgwc=/0x0:1020x676/1420x947/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1420w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0NtXMcconWS4cEgprnAXyqsEYlM=/0x0:1020x676/1520x1013/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1520w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/eWed6vNmCllnNHlcmYf8JUY7NFA=/0x0:1020x676/1620x1080/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1620w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0Edvnf1i6Ovte6utpD7700eFrnA=/0x0:1020x676/1720x1147/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1720w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Q4HQCeFGrtGpmUathPVwAvOxszU=/0x0:1020x676/1820x1213/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1820w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/rkHkuObGwHk5AhOESPproCAUP64=/0x0:1020x676/1920x1280/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 1920w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f6wLVI0BULmrYCiMdxgAfP-KTjQ=/0x0:1020x676/2020x1347/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 2020w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9ZrHD5JRjlOzrdQxzT0oo7YB4v0=/0x0:1020x676/2120x1413/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 2120w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Mi0Y2sJ-FCEGNCVo9uFNtlDYWj8=/0x0:1020x676/2220x1480/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 2220w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/t0ht0GuThh6rQTUdXgq78K3VZV4=/0x0:1020x676/2320x1547/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 2320w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jVR1g4nQDYYkoDWJaRa6wHjWey8=/0x0:1020x676/2420x1613/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 2420w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Xh3Ym5f65KoD2EzmkatFCxCIyPg=/0x0:1020x676/2520x1680/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 2520w, https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/M0hwIktPF1Iiq1MzFpDZ33T6s0Q=/0x0:1020x676/2620x1747/filters:focal(429x257:591x419)/cdn3.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51773567/2012-09-12timcook-iphone5-27.0.jpg 2620w\" /></picture></span></figure> <div class=\"c-entry-content\"> <p id=\"k1sTmx\">Over the past 24 hours, top executives at Apple, eBay, Box, LinkedIn, and Microsoft have all sent company-wide memos&nbsp;urging employees to try to move forward, and expressing the belief that people are inherently good. Others, like Facebook&rsquo;s Mark Zuckerberg, have&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.theverge.com/2016/11/10/13582008/mark-zuckerberg-facebook-trump-president-statement\">posted public statements</a> about having to find new ways to work together. It&rsquo;s the kind of messaging that a company leader would send after a natural disaster, an attack on the nation, or a looming crisis within the company.</p> <p id=\"mgLMHj\">Only this time, the looming crisis is the president-elect.</p> <p id=\"GeoXHP\">The fact that CEOs are compelled to communicate with employees following this year&rsquo;s election shows how rattled Silicon Valley is. It&rsquo;s been an <a href=\"http://www.recode.net/2016/11/9/13576446/ebay-ceo-memo-us-election-diversity\">\"emotionally-charged election,\" </a>as eBay&rsquo;s Devin Wenig wrote, an <a href=\"https://medium.com/@levie/quick-thoughts-on-the-election-77821a10a5a1#.d1792y6qi\">\"emotional roller coaster of toxic rhetoric\"</a> according to Box&rsquo;s Aaron Levie, the aftermath of which is <a href=\"https://www.buzzfeed.com/johnpaczkowski/read-tim-cooks-email-to-apple-employees-after-donald-trumps\">\"leaving many of you with strong feelings,\"</a> as Apple&rsquo;s Tim Cook wrote. LinkedIn\'s Jeff Weiner wrote that \"<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/my-thoughts-election-jeff-weiner\" target=\"_blank\">polarization and open hostility was sustained for so long</a> that people with opposing views became more caricature than actual human beings.\"</p> <p><q class=\"center\">THE KIND OF MESSAGING YOU\'D EXPECT TO SEE AFTER A NATURAL DISASTER OR CRISIS WITHIN THE COMPANY</q></p> <p id=\"l5T7sK\">Sure, CEOs have congratulated president-elects before, and <a href=\"http://www.theverge.com/2016/11/10/13585614/bezos-congratulates-amazon-and-washington-post-hater-donald-trump\">are doing that now</a>. They&rsquo;ve marked momentous and historic occasions with tweets and letters and opinion pieces. But this is different. This time, a presidential candidate has run a divisive campaign that simultaneously appealed to working-class voters and alienated many others who felt &mdash; who still feel &mdash; threatened by the racist, misogynistic, and authoritarian views he has expressed.</p> <p id=\"yHY4Jl\">More pointedly for Silicon Valley, Donald Trump&rsquo;s jabs at the tech industry have often been antagonistic. He&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.recode.net/2016/2/19/11588048/donald-trump-calls-for-apple-boycott\">called for a boycott of Apple products</a> over the company&rsquo;s dispute with the FBI in the wake of the San Bernardino tragedy, has accused social media companies of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/792734426912337920\">burying news about Hillary Clinton</a>, has <a href=\"http://www.computerworld.com/article/3139394/it-careers/at-campaigns-end-trump-takes-a-swipe-at-ibm.html\">called out tech companies for moving jobs overseas</a>, and has taken <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/10/us/politics/donald-trump-taxes-climate-immigration-health-care.html?_r=0\">an overt anti-immigration stance</a>, a stark contrast to the tech sector&rsquo;s embrace of high-skill visa programs that bring in foreign talent. (It&rsquo;s also possible &mdash; and perhaps likely &mdash; that some of Trump&rsquo;s policies could be beneficial to tech companies, like a <a href=\"http://www.marketwatch.com/story/apple-and-trump-can-a-tax-cut-for-overseas-cash-heal-wounds-2016-11-09\">so-called tax holiday</a> for the money companies have been hoarding overseas.)</p> <p id=\"Bxjgvk\">Arguably, these notes from top executives to their thousands of employees might have held more weight if they were sent out <em>before</em> the election, not as responses to an outcome. But doing so might have alienated employees, or carried the tone of telling them who to vote for. Some CEOs may have been concerned that vocalizing their thoughts around a contentious election would have impacted their business, although the particular irony of that will now be determined by how a Trump presidency affects the broader economy.</p> <p><q class=\"center\">SILICON VALLEY WAS CAUGHT FLAT-FOOTED AND OPEN-MOUTHED IN THE WAKE OF A TRAUMATIZING ELECTION SEASON</q></p> <p id=\"S4bgxQ\">Even if they had expressed these thoughts beforehand, it still might not have mattered: Silicon Valley was, and still is, in its own echo chamber, caught flat-footed and open-mouthed in the wake of a traumatizing election season; building cool new products for people every day but having underestimated the extent to which people were willing to vote for a productized presidential candidate, one who at some level rejects their techno-utopianism.</p> <p>The notes being shared so far carry hopeful tones. Box CEO Levie reiterated the company&rsquo;s values of \"openness and inclusion.\" Apple&rsquo;s Cook said the company&rsquo;s \"North Star hasn&rsquo;t changed,\" and also included an inspiring quote from Martin Luther King Jr. eBay&rsquo;s Wenig said to \"stay focused.\" CEOs have a particular interest in keeping employees motivated to do work, and in offering the support that enable employees to do this. All of us, tech employees or otherwise, have to wake up, get out of bed, and go about our days.</p> <p id=\"5YQqft\">But it&rsquo;s the subtext and the context that are most meaningful: the fact that they&rsquo;re writing these letters in the first place. They want to remind people that their workplaces are diverse, and that they should show mutual respect for each other. They&rsquo;re asking them to work together in the spirit of generosity. They now feel compelled to tell their employees to just <em>be kind </em>to each other. <em>Please, let&rsquo;s be decent to one another.</em> This election season has brought us all to this point, whether in Silicon Valley, or anywhere else.</p> </div> </div> </div>',NULL,'Lauren Goode','Recode',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(6,'Vudu\'s upgraded mobile app brings offline rental viewing','You can also watch extras, buy discs and AirPlay your videos.',11,2,'2016-11-13 06:47:00','https://s.aolcdn.com/dims5/amp:1e2655ec8979a0c479aa195a1603e11446c21baa/t:1200,630/q:80/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fs.aolcdn.com%2Fhss%2Fstorage%2Fmidas%2F1e313ebe72146ea35f8d4112aa10104b%2F204580550%2Fvudu-ios-5.jpg',1,'<header class=\"o-feed_listing@m- o-feed_bleed@m- mb-10@m mb-40@tp+\"> <div class=\"o-feed_listing@m-__mid\"> <div class=\"o-feed_listing@m-__inner break-left@m- bg-white@m-\"> <div class=\"o-title_mark@tp+ bc-gray-1 col-10-of-12@tl+\"> <h1 class=\"t-h4@m- t-h1-b@tp t-h1@tl+ mt-20 mt-15@tp mt-0@m-\">Vudu\'s upgraded mobile app brings offline rental viewing</h1> <h2 class=\"t-d7@m- t-d4@tp t-d3-b@tl t-d2@d mt-15 mt-25@tp c-gray-3 c-gray-6@m-\">You can also watch extras, buy discs and AirPlay your videos.</h2> </div> <section class=\"o-meta_bar@tl+ mt-35 mt-20@m-\"> <div class=\"grid@tl+\">&nbsp;</div> </section> </div> </div> </header> <div id=\"page_body\"> <div class=\"container@m-\"> <div class=\"flush-top flush-bottom\" data-behavior=\"FitVids \"> <div class=\"o-article_block \"> <div class=\"grid@tl+ mt-n40\"> <div>&nbsp;</div> <div id=\"right-ads-rail\" class=\"hide@tp- grid@tl+__cell col-4-of-12@tl+ right@tl+ flush-top pt-40 relative z-1\"> <aside id=\"shared-ads-container\"> <div class=\"vc relative mb-20\">&nbsp;</div> </aside> <div id=\"taboola-right-rail-thumbnails\" class=\"mt-35 mb-35 trc_related_container trc_spotlight_widget trc_elastic trc_elastic_trc_52322 \" data-placement-name=\"Right Rail Thumbnails\">&nbsp;</div> <aside> <div class=\"relative mb-15 mt-25\">&nbsp;</div> </aside> </div> <div class=\"grid@tl+__cell col-8-of-12@tl+ pt-40 hide@m-\"> <figure><img class=\"stretch-img hide@m-\" src=\"https://s.aolcdn.com/dims5/amp:030d6c8b91b128f84ac5c7780f7269c056d26db9/q:100/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fo.aolcdn.com%2Fhss%2Fstorage%2Fmidas%2F1e313ebe72146ea35f8d4112aa10104b%2F204580550%2Fvudu-ios-5.jpg\" /></figure> </div> </div> </div> <div class=\"o-article_block pb-15 pb-5@m- o-subtle_divider\"> <div class=\"grid@tl+\"> <div class=\"grid@tl+__cell col-8-of-12@tl+\"> <div class=\"article-text c-gray-1\"> <p>Unlike <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2016/11/02/netflix-offline-playback/\">some big streaming video services</a>, Vudu isn\'t sitting on the fence when it comes to offline playback. The Walmart-owned provider has <a href=\"http://blog.vudu.com/?p=12001\">revamped</a> its Android and iOS apps with several big features, most notably an option to download your rentals -- you can watch that movie in mid-flight even when the <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2016/02/22/american-airlines-drops-lawsuit-against-gogo/\">in-air WiFi is lousy</a>. You\'ll also have access to movie extras for supporting titles, and iOS users now get both higher-quality <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2015/10/11/vudu-1080p-hdx-movies-android/\">1080p HDX streaming</a> as well as AirPlay. And if you\'re still attached to hard copies, you can buy discs inside the app instead of heading to the web. So long as you live in the US and like Vudu\'s <em>&agrave; la carte</em> approach to movies and TV, you can check out the upgrade right now.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>',NULL,'Jon Fingas','Engadget',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(7,'Apple addresses ‘Touch Disease’ with reduced cost repair for iPhone 6 Plus','Many an iPhone 6 Plus has been struck down by the scourge known as \\\"Touch Disease,\\\" but Apple has not acknowledged the problem was systematic or widespread..',10,2,'2016-11-17 22:39:52','https://tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com/2015/09/iphone-6s-plus-31.jpg',1,'<header class=\"article-header page-title\"> <h1 class=\"alpha tweet-title\">Apple addresses &lsquo;Touch Disease&rsquo; with reduced cost repair for iPhone 6 Plus</h1> <div class=\"title-left\"> <div class=\"byline\">Posted <time class=\"timestamp\" datetime=\"2016-11-17\">Nov 17, 2016</time> by <a title=\"Posts by Devin Coldewey\" href=\"https://techcrunch.com/author/devin-coldewey/\" rel=\"author\">Devin Coldewey</a>, Contributor</div> <div class=\"social-share social-share-inline\">&nbsp;</div> </div> <div class=\"next-story-link\">Next Story</div> <div class=\"next-story-full\"> <h4 class=\"next-title\">Handshake nabs another $20M to make the job hunt more&nbsp;fair</h4> </div> </header> <div class=\"l-two-col\"> <div class=\"l-main-container\"> <div class=\"l-main\"> <div class=\"article-entry text\"><img class=\"\" src=\"https://tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com/2015/09/iphone-6s-plus-31.jpg?w=1372\" /> <p>Many an iPhone 6 Plus has been struck down by the scourge known as &ldquo;Touch Disease,&rdquo; but Apple has not acknowledged the problem was systematic or widespread &mdash; until now. In what we have to imagine is as close to a mea culpa as Apple is likely to offer, iPhone 6 Plus devices exhibiting flickering displays and touchscreen issues are <a href=\"http://www.apple.com/support/iphone6plus-multitouch/\" target=\"_blank\">eligible for a reduced-price repair</a>.</p> <p>Apple is careful to note that this problem mainly appears &ldquo;after being dropped multiple times on a hard surface and then incurring further stress,&rdquo; though <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2016/08/29/sufferers-of-iphone-6s-touch-disease-may-soon-have-a-class-action-lawsuit/\" target=\"_blank\">iFixit suggested</a> that the problem could also be due to the phone&rsquo;s infamous <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2014/09/23/the-iphone-6-plus-gets-bent/\" target=\"_blank\">tendency to bend</a>. Either way, some force must be exerted on the phone, resulting reliably in a critical touchscreen component being damaged or unseated &mdash; and that makes it, like it or not, at least partially a user-caused issue. Apple declining to call it a design flaw or manufacturing defect seems to be a point of pride on their part.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <div class=\"aside aside-related-articles\"> <h2>Related Articles</h2> <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2016/08/29/sufferers-of-iphone-6s-touch-disease-may-soon-have-a-class-action-lawsuit/\">Sufferers of iPhone 6\'s \'Touch Disease\' may soon have a class action lawsuit</a><a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2014/09/23/the-iphone-6-plus-gets-bent/\">The iPhone 6 Plus Gets Bent</a><a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2016/09/16/inside-the-iphone-7/\">There&rsquo;s an Intel modem and an extremely skinny A10 chip inside the iPhone 7</a></div> Phones with Touch Disease will be repaired for $149, and if you previously had it repaired or replaced for similar symptoms &mdash; which might have cost you upwards of $300 &mdash; Apple will reimburse you the difference. <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>iFixit pointed out in an email to TechCrunch that this price is about what third-party repairers have charged in the past to fix the issue, and considering refurbished phones are subject to the same problem, the 90-day warranty is rather short.</p> <p>Notably, the program is only for the iPhone 6 Plus, and although a similar problem has been seen on the 6, we can probably trust Apple&rsquo;s numbers and say this was primarily an issue with the Plus.</p> <div>&nbsp;</div> <p>It certainly took long enough: It&rsquo;s been more than two years since the 6 Plus was announced, and Apple never addressed the Touch Disease issue, despite it being quite common &mdash; and despite quietly reinforcing the next generation of iPhones to prevent the problem (the one they didn&rsquo;t publicly acknowledge) from occurring again.</p> <p>In fact, it was long enough that a <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2016/08/29/sufferers-of-iphone-6s-touch-disease-may-soon-have-a-class-action-lawsuit/\" target=\"_blank\">lawsuit was filed </a>alleging that Apple knew the problem existed and failed to provide adequate support to affected users. I contacted the law firm leading that suit to see if the repair program affects it in any way, and will update this post if I hear back.</p> <p>Better late than never, though, and covering previous repairs is generous by Apple standards. Drop by an Apple store or authorized dealer, or talk to tech support to get your afflicted iPhone 6 Plus back in action.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div>',NULL,'Devin Coldewey','TechCrunch',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(8,'Google`s new Pixel phone case will put the day`s news where you can`t avoid it','Google is releasing two Live phone cases for its Pixel today that not only look nice on phones but also change the wallpaper daily. The more logical of the cases is Google Earth-themed',10,1,'2016-11-17 22:20:26','https://cdn0.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kea-v8W7HuLofPPaBntxbBYgRUs=/29x0:971x530/1600x900/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51891287/LiveCase_Pixel_Combo.width_1000.0.png',1,'<div class=\"l-segment\"> <div class=\"c-entry-hero c-entry-hero--default\"> <div class=\"c-entry-hero__header-wrap\"> <h1 class=\"c-page-title\">Google\'s new Pixel phone case will put the day\'s news where you can\'t avoid it</h1> </div> <div class=\"c-byline\">by <span class=\"c-byline__item\"><a href=\"http://www.theverge.com/users/ashleycarman\">Ashley Carman</a><a class=\"c-byline__twitter-handle\" href=\"http://www.twitter.com/ashleyrcarman\">@ashleyrcarman</a> </span><time class=\"c-byline__item\" data-ui=\"timestamp\"> Nov 17, 2016, 5:20pm EST</time></div> </div> </div> <div class=\"l-sidebar-fixed l-segment\"> <div class=\"l-col__main\"> <figure class=\"e-image e-image--hero\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn1.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/51891289/LiveCase_Pixel_Combo.width_1000.0.png\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1483354826_6549_58018\" 